      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "f341131c_00a8abf3",
      "file_path": "src/k8splugin/internal/app/instance.go",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 255,
      "message": "Couple thoughts -\n1 - the v2 version of status does not differentiate\n2 - the collection of resource status is simply the list of resources that match the given label, the pods resulting from Deployments, etc. are still in this category.\n\nThat said, is there a potential use for keeping the dynamic pods separate - e.g. I want to look through that list for some purpose and don't want to always filter out the rest?\n\nSo, I'm ok with all labeled resources together - but open to hear reasons to keep separate.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1603,
        "name": "Eric Multanen",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "eric.w.multanen@intel.com",
        "username": "ewmulta"
      },
      "updated": "2020-09-30 17:29:41.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "572be23b_3f77ee6d",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "e3d647c1_838113c2",
      "file_path": "src/k8splugin/internal/app/instance.go",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 255,
      "message": "The only reasoning is that we have static resources comming from helm and dynamic like Pods created indireclty. From API consumer perspective processing of both may be different so maybe it is worth to give separate access to both sets. Like said, I have no clear opinion. So at the end I leave it for your decision whether to change it or not.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2701,
        "name": "Lukasz Rajewski",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "lukasz.rajewski@t-mobile.pl",
        "username": "rajewluk"
      },
      "updated": "2020-09-30 20:51:28.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "f341131c_00a8abf3",
      "unresolved": true
    },
